-- IG Metall Head ‘Confident’ on Salary Increase, Berliner Reports
-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 2012-03-24T00:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-24/ig-metall-head-confident-on-salary-increase-berliner-reports.html
Germany ’s IG Metall labor union is
“confident” it will manage to get a “significant” pay
increase in the current round of wage negotiations for the metal
and electronic industries, Berthold Huber, the union’s head,
said in an interview with Berliner Zeitung.  IG Metall is asking for 6.5 percent “more money,” the
German newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
